				<name type="primary" sortindex="1" value="アミーゴ！ (AMIGO!)" />
			
						                           
						               													<description>&amp;#227;&amp;#130;&amp;#162;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#159;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#188;&amp;#227;&amp;#130;&amp;#180;&amp;#239;&amp;#188;&amp;#129; (AMIGO!) is a Japanese speed word game. Players must determine the start letter of a word, then call out a word that fits the chosen theme.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each player has two thumbs up cards. After a theme card and a word card card are turned up, players choose how to play their thumb cards. A thumb up is +1, a thumb down is -1. All players reveal their thumbs (you don't have to use both) and work out the correct number of steps.&amp;#10;4 thumbs up and 0 thumbs down equals +4 steps on the word card, giving the start letter. &amp;#10;2 thumbs up and 4 thumbs down equals -2 steps on the word card (starting at the end of the word and going backwards), giving the start letter.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;If the total of thumbs is zero, everybody shouts &amp;quot;AMIGO!&amp;quot;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The first player to get a word fitting the theme and start letter gives their answer. If correct, they get the theme card. If wrong, they hand one back as a penalty.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The player with the most theme cards collected by the end is the winner.&amp;#10;user summary&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
